name: Bernard Hill

name: HECS
summary: The Australian government is implementing significant changes to the Higher Education Loan Program (HELP), commonly known as HECS. The positive news is that $3 billion in student debt will be canceled. However, concerns remain as the interest rate (indexation) on remaining debt will still be high. This has prompted criticism, as highlighted in articles such as "HELP! We've Been HECS'd" and "The HECS debt system has been broken for a long time." The government aims to overhaul the indexation system and provide a one-off $1,200 boost to millions of Australians affected by HECS/HELP debt. These changes will be outlined in the upcoming May 14 budget.
